title: Subarray sum equals k (only positive integers)
content:
class Solution:
    def subarraySum(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:

        left = 0
        right = 0
        window_sum = 0
        count = 0

        while right < len(nums):
            
            # add the right to the window
            window_sum += nums[right]

            # shrink the window untill we have sum < k
            while window_sum > k:
                window_sum -= nums[left]
                left += 1

            # if current window has sum equal to k
            if window_sum == k:
                count += 1
            
            # expand the window
            right += 1

        return count

content:
-- Laser-Guided Warp System (“ztc”) with H/I/O prompts and O-key to run otc

-- 1) Wrap terminal + any attached monitors
local screens = {}

-- Terminal wrapper
table.insert(screens, {
  clear              = function() term.clear(); term.setCursorPos(1,1) end,
  getSize            = function() return term.getSize() end,
  setTextColor       = term.setTextColor,
  setBackgroundColor = term.setBackgroundColor,
  setCursorPos       = term.setCursorPos,
  write              = term.write,
})

-- Monitor wrappers
for _, side in ipairs(peripheral.getNames()) do
  if peripheral.getType(side) == "monitor" then
    local m = peripheral.wrap(side)
    table.insert(screens, {
      clear              = function() m.clear(); m.setCursorPos(1,1) end,
      getSize            = function() return m.getSize() end,
      setTextColor       = function(c) m.setTextColor(c) end,
      setBackgroundColor = function(c) m.setBackgroundColor(c) end,
      setCursorPos       = function(x,y) m.setCursorPos(x,y) end,
      write              = function(txt) m.write(txt) end,
      monitor            = m,
    })
  end
end

-- 2) Auto-scale monitors so at least 7 lines will fit
for _, s in ipairs(screens) do
  if s.monitor then
    local best = 0.5
    for _, scale in ipairs({1, 0.5}) do
      s.monitor.setTextScale(scale)
      local w,h = s.getSize()
      if w >= 40 and h >= 7 then
        best = scale
        break
      end
    end
    s.monitor.setTextScale(best)
  end
end

-- 3) Helpers
local function forAll(fn) for _,s in ipairs(screens) do fn(s) end end

-- Clear every screen to lightGray
local function clearAll()
  forAll(function(s)
    s.setTextColor(colors.black)
    s.setBackgroundColor(colors.lightGray)
    s.clear()
  end)
end

-- 4) Static texts
local titleText     = "Horizontal Mining System"
local subtitleText  = "Emit Scanning Laser to Mine Target"
local offsetText    = "Mining Laser Offset ( I ): "
local promptH       = "Press H for Main Menu"
local promptI       = "Press C to Configure Miner"
local promptO       = "Press L to Toggle Miner"

-- track offset state
local isOffsetOn = false

-- Draw title, subtitle, and offset-state line (now on line 5)
local function drawStatic()
  forAll(function(s)
    local w,_ = s.getSize()
    -- Title (line 1): white on black
    local xT = math.floor((w - #titleText)/2) + 1
    s.setTextColor(colors.white)
    s.setBackgroundColor(colors.black)
    s.setCursorPos(xT,1)
    s.write(titleText)

    -- Subtitle (line 3): black on lightGray
    local xS = math.floor((w - #subtitleText)/2) + 1
    s.setTextColor(colors.black)
    s.setBackgroundColor(colors.lightGray)
    s.setCursorPos(xS,3)
    s.write(subtitleText)

    -- (line 4 is intentionally left blank)

    -- Mining Laser Offset (line 5)
    local statusText = isOffsetOn and "ON" or "OFF"
    local fullOffset = offsetText .. statusText
    local xO = math.floor((w - #fullOffset)/2) + 1

    -- background bar
    s.setTextColor(colors.black)
    s.setBackgroundColor(colors.lightGray)
    s.setCursorPos(1,5)
    s.write(string.rep(" ", w))

    -- label
    s.setCursorPos(xO,5)
    s.write(offsetText)

    -- ON vs OFF coloring
    s.setTextColor(colors.white)
    s.setBackgroundColor(isOffsetOn and colors.lime or colors.red)
    s.write(statusText)
  end)
end

-- Draw prompts on the bottom three rows
local function drawPrompt()
  forAll(function(s)
    local w,h = s.getSize()
    -- line h-2: O prompt
    s.setTextColor(colors.white)
    s.setBackgroundColor(colors.blue)
    s.setCursorPos(1,h-2)
    s.write(string.rep(" ", w))
    local xO = math.floor((w - #promptO)/2) + 1
    s.setCursorPos(xO,h-2)
    s.write(promptO)
    -- line h-1: H prompt
    s.setTextColor(colors.white)
    s.setBackgroundColor(colors.blue)
    s.setCursorPos(1,h-1)
    s.write(string.rep(" ", w))
    local xH = math.floor((w - #promptH)/2) + 1
    s.setCursorPos(xH,h-1)
    s.write(promptH)
    -- line h: I prompt
    s.setBackgroundColor(colors.blue)
    s.setCursorPos(1,h)
    s.write(string.rep(" ", w))
    local xI = math.floor((w - #promptI)/2) + 1
    s.setCursorPos(xI,h)
    s.write(promptI)
  end)
end

-- 5) Set up all modems for rednet, then broadcast a startup check
for _, side in ipairs(peripheral.getNames()) do
  if peripheral.getType(side) == "modem" then
    rednet.open(side)
  end
end
rednet.broadcast("check", "SMiner")

-- now set up warpdriveLaserCamera peripherals
local cams = peripheral.getNames()
for i=#cams,1,-1 do
  if peripheral.getType(cams[i]) ~= "warpdriveLaserCamera" then
    table.remove(cams,i)
  else
    peripheral.wrap(cams[i]).beamFrequency(1420)
  end
end

-- 6) Initial draw (blank coords)
clearAll()
drawStatic()
drawPrompt()

-- 7) Coords line, accepts nil → blanks before first scan (on line 6)
local function updateCoords(x,y,z)
  local sx = x and tostring(x) or "    "
  local sy = y and tostring(y) or "    "
  local sz = z and tostring(z) or "    "
  local coordLine = string.format("Target: X:%s   Y:%s   Z:%s", sx, sy, sz)
  forAll(function(s)
    local w,_ = s.getSize()
    s.setTextColor(colors.black)
    s.setBackgroundColor(colors.lightGray)
    s.setCursorPos(1,6)
    s.write(string.rep(" ", w))
    local cx = math.floor((w - #coordLine)/2) + 1
    s.setCursorPos(cx,6)
    s.write(coordLine)
  end)
end

-- draw initial blanks (on line 6)
updateCoords(nil,nil,nil)

-- keep last coords around for redraws
local lastX, lastY, lastZ = nil, nil, nil

-- 8) Main loop: scan + key handling + status listener
while true do
  -- 8a) non-blocking check for SMiner status messages
  local sender, msg, proto = rednet.receive("SMiner", 0)
  if msg == "StatON" then
    isOffsetOn = true
    clearAll(); drawStatic(); updateCoords(lastX,lastY,lastZ); drawPrompt()
  elseif msg == "StatOFF" then
    isOffsetOn = false
    clearAll(); drawStatic(); updateCoords(lastX,lastY,lastZ); drawPrompt()
  end

  -- 8b) main events
  local ev,k,b,c,d = os.pullEventRaw()
  if ev == "laserScanning" then
    lastX = tonumber(b)
    lastY = tonumber(c)
    lastZ = tonumber(d)
    updateCoords(lastX,lastY,lastZ)
    rednet.broadcast({ x = lastX, y = lastY, z = lastZ }, "SMineBroadcast")

  elseif ev == "key" then
    if k == keys.h then
      os.reboot()
    elseif k == keys.c then
      shell.run("conf")
      clearAll(); drawStatic(); updateCoords(lastX,lastY,lastZ); drawPrompt()
    elseif k == keys.l then
      rednet.broadcast("Toggle","SMiner")
    end
  end
end

-- Improved WarpDrive Miner Control Script (fixed wrap error)

-- Initialization
term.clear()

-- Find the laser peripheral (returns wrapped table)
local laser = peripheral.find("warpdriveLaser")
if not laser then
  print("No warpdriveLaser detected")
  return
end

-- Find mining lasers by name and wrap them
local miningLasers = {}
for _, side in ipairs(peripheral.getNames()) do
  if peripheral.getType(side) == "warpdriveMiningLaser" then
    table.insert(miningLasers, peripheral.wrap(side))
  end
end
if #miningLasers == 0 then
  print("No warpdriveMiningLaser detected")
  return
end

-- Set the laser frequency
laser.beamFrequency(1420)

-- Persistence helpers
local function saveZeroLayersCount(cnt)
  local f = fs.open("zero_layers.txt", "w")
  f.write(tostring(cnt))
  f.close()
end

local function getZeroLayersCount()
  if fs.exists("zero_layers.txt") then
    local f = fs.open("zero_layers.txt", "r")
    local c = tonumber(f.readAll())
    f.close()
    return c or 0
  end
  return 0
end

print("Press 'M' to scan & start mining")

-- Main loop
while true do
  local _, key = os.pullEvent("key")
  if key == keys.m then
    -- Emit scan
    local _, laserY = laser.getLocalPosition()
    local targetY
    repeat
      laser.emitBeam(0, -1, 0)
      os.sleep(1)
      local x, y, z = laser.getScanResult()
      targetY = z
    until targetY ~= 0

    local offset = laserY - targetY - 1
    print(("Offset: %d"):format(offset))

    -- Activate mining lasers
    for _, ml in ipairs(miningLasers) do
      ml.offset(offset)
      ml.enable(true)
    end

    -- Monitor and auto-stop after 3 empty layers
    local zeros = getZeroLayersCount()
    while true do
      os.sleep(1)
      local st, active, energy, layer, mined, total = miningLasers[1].state()
      if total == 0 then zeros = zeros + 1 else zeros = 0 end
      saveZeroLayersCount(zeros)
      if zeros >= 3 then
        print("3 empty layers → stopping mining")
        for _, ml in ipairs(miningLasers) do ml.enable(false) end
        fs.delete("zero_layers.txt")
        break
      end
    end

    print("Press 'M' to scan & start mining")
  end
end
